The paper deals with the problem of random access in grammar compressed strings, which is a fundamental problem in data structures. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper introduces new techniques for decomposing grammars and improving the longest common extension problem, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of "Information Theory" (cs.IT), "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC), "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DC), and "Machine Learning" (cs.LG).
